  "content_id": "53b1f95d-fe8c-4bf8-8f89-875b6f115105",
  "description": "The Competition and Markets Authority (CMA) may investigate a merger between your business and another to make sure it’s fair",
  "details": {
    "body": "\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>The Competition and Markets Authority (CMA) may investigate a merger between your business and another to make sure it’s fair.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>A merger usually only qualifies for a <a href=\"/government/publications/mergers-guidance-on-the-cmas-jurisdiction-and-procedure\"><abbr title=\"Competition and Markets Authority\">CMA</abbr> investigation</a> if either:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the business being taken over has a UK annual turnover of at least £70 million</li>\n  <li>the combined businesses have at least a 25% share of any reasonable market</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Merging businesses includes acquisitions, take-overs and joint ventures.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Find out more about <abbr title=\"Competition and Markets Authority\">CMA</abbr>’s <a href=\"/government/publications/merger-assessment-guidelines\">merger assessment guidelines</a>, and the <a href=\"/government/publications/merger-remedies\">prohibitions and remedies</a> that can be applied.</p>\n\n",
    "external_related_links": [

    ]
  },
